{
  "profile_id": "client-red-herring-more-money-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v3-embeddings",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I've been grinding for ten years. If I could just get to a certain level of savings I'd be done. But every time I get close the number moves. How do I push through this last bit?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That number has moved before. What makes you think this time it stays still?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "That's... fair. I mean, it's different now. I'm at 1.4 million in liquid assets, the house is paid off, income's around 180 a year. The math actually works this time. I've modeled it out -- 4% withdrawal rate, conservative projections, it holds. So the number isn't arbitrary. It's 1.8. I get to 1.8 and the math is solid."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What happens to you when you imagine actually stopping?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I'd finally have options. I could write the book I've been putting off, probably for -- god, eight years now. Take care of my parents without the stress of whether I can afford it. Travel. Just... breathe, I guess.\n\nI mean, the 1.8 isn't about stopping necessarily. It's about having the choice. That's what I'm after. The choice."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You have the choice right now.\n\nWhat's stopping you from writing the book?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I don't have the runway. If something happened -- a health issue, my parents needing significant care, a market correction -- I'd be exposed. 1.4 doesn't have enough buffer.\n\nAnd the book isn't going to make money, at least not initially. So I'd be drawing down while producing nothing, and that... that's hard to sit with."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "So the choice you're after — you already have it. You could stop tomorrow. What's actually in the way is that stopping feels dangerous.\n\nWhat's the feeling underneath \"exposed\"?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "It's not irrational, though. The numbers are real. A serious health event, long-term care for two parents -- those costs are documented. I've run the scenarios.\n\nBut... yeah. Okay. There's something that doesn't feel like math. When I imagine actually stopping, there's this -- I don't know. Like the floor might not hold. Even when I know it will.\n\nIt's probably just prudence. I've always been careful with money. That's how you get to 1.4."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "\"The floor might not hold\" — that's not prudence. Prudence is in the spreadsheet. That feeling is something older.\n\nWhere did you first learn that the floor might not hold?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean... my dad worked hard. Really hard. Two jobs for a while when I was a kid. We weren't -- it wasn't dire, but it was close enough that you felt it. You felt when things were tight.\n\nHe didn't talk about it directly. But you knew. The way he'd get quiet at the kitchen table. The way certain conversations just stopped.\n\n*pause*\n\nI don't know that that's relevant here. I've done the work. I'm not in that situation."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You're not in that situation. And your body still learned something at that kitchen table that it hasn't forgotten.\n\nWhat did young you decide about what it meant to be safe?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*longer pause*\n\nThat you had to earn it. Safety. You couldn't just... have it. You had to produce enough that the quiet at the kitchen table never happened.\n\nI think I decided that if you were careful enough, if you worked hard enough, you'd get to a place where that feeling stopped.\n\n*quieter*\n\nI've been waiting for it to stop."
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "Yeah.\n\nAnd it hasn't stopped, has it. Not at 1.4. Not at 1.8 either, probably."
    },
    {
      "turn": 15,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*quiet for a moment*\n\nNo. It hasn't.\n\nI mean -- logically I know that. That's why I'm here, probably. The number keeps moving and I keep telling myself the next one is the real one.\n\nBut that's just... that's a planning problem, right? I need a better framework for knowing when enough is enough. That's a solvable thing.\n\n*slight tension returning*\n\nThere has to be a point where the math actually does the job."
    }
  ],
